name: Breadless Stuffing Quiche
author: cindycbryan
summary: If you are counting carbs or just craving the flavors of Thanksgiving stuffing, this recipe is for you! I love serving this on a bed of arugula leaves!
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C)
Heat oil in a saucepan over medium-high heat
Saute onions in the hot oil until softened and lightly browned, about 5 minutes
Add celery and cook until soft, about 5 minutes; stir in chicken broth, garlic, parsley, sage, rosemary, and thyme
Simmer broth mixture until it thickens slightly, about 10 minutes
Remove saucepan from heat and pour broth mixture into a bowl
Set it aside to cool, about 10 minutes
Stir eggs and feta cheese into broth mixture; pour into the prepared pan
Bake in the preheated oven until set, 25 to 35 minutes
